<h3>The Zero-Click Problem</h3>
<p>Over 65% of Google searches now end without a click to any website. Users find their answer directly on the results page. This is the zero-click phenomenon.</p>
<p>It does not mean SEO is dying. It means the type of content that earns clicks has changed. Generic definitions lose. Deep, opinionated, data-rich content wins because users need more than a snippet can provide.</p>
